<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>How To - Eldoria Arcane Registry of Deeds</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/global.css">
    <style>
        .guide-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; }
        .guide-table th { background: #2a5278; color: #fff; padding: 7px 10px; text-align: left; font-size: 12px; }
        .guide-table td { padding: 7px 10px; vertical-align: middle; font-size: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; }
        .guide-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background-color: #E3EAEB; }
        .badge { display: inline-block; background: #2a5278; color: #fff; font-family: Courier, monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: bold; padding: 2px 7px; margin-right: 6px; }
        .guide-desc { color: #444; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="container">
        <div class="headerBar">Grand Duchy of Eldoria - Arcane Registry of Deeds</div>

        <div class="navBar">
            <a href="/l1/taxes/">Home</a>
            <a href="/l1/taxes/tax-search">Tax Search</a>
            <a href="/l1/taxes/how-to">How To</a>
        </div>

        <div class="breadcrumbs">
            <a href="/l1/taxes/">Home</a> &gt; How To Guides
        </div>

        <div class="pageTitle">How To: Document Filing Guides</div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <p>
                The Grand Duchy of Eldoria Arcane Registry of Deeds publishes the following official guides
                for property owners, attorneys, contractors, and clan representatives. Each guide covers
                the purpose, required elements, filing process, and common pitfalls for a specific
                document type. Click <strong>View Guide</strong> to read the full guide as a PDF.
            </p>

            <table class="guide-table">
                <tr>
                    <th style="width: 80px;">Index Type</th>
                    <th>Guide Title</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    <th style="width: 90px;">Actions</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">DEED</span></td>
                    <td>Recording a Deed</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">How to transfer title to subterranean real property — warranty deeds, quitclaim deeds, trustee's deeds, required elements, and filing steps.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-deed.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">MTG</span></td>
                    <td>Filing and Managing a Mortgage</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">How to record a mortgage, required uniform covenants, and how to obtain a satisfaction once the loan is paid in full.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-mtg.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">LIEN</span></td>
                    <td>Filing a Mechanic's Lien</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">Who may file, statutory deadlines, Notice to Owner requirements, Schedule A itemization, and how to contest or release a lien.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-lien.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">ESMT</span></td>
                    <td>Registering an Easement</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">How to create and record utility, access, drainage, and magma-routing easements including coordinate description requirements.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-esmt.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">ASGN</span></td>
                    <td>Filing an Assignment of Mortgage</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">How to transfer a mortgage lien to a new holder, required elements, Mortgagor notification rules, and partial assignments.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-asgn.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">REL</span></td>
                    <td>Releasing a Lien or Mortgage</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">Mortgagee obligations upon payoff, step-by-step release process, penalties for delayed discharge, and judicial release procedures.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-rel.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">NTC</span></td>
                    <td>Filing a Notice of Commencement</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">When a NOC is required, what to include, job-site posting requirements, and how to amend or terminate a NOC after project completion.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-ntc.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge">AFF</span></td>
                    <td>Filing an Affidavit of Title</td>
                    <td class="guide-desc">What must be disclosed, legal consequences of false statements, and how to prepare and record a sworn title affidavit.</td>
                    <td><a href="/how-to/how-to-aff.pdf" target="_blank">View Guide</a></td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Need Additional Assistance?</strong><br>
            <span class="aspNetLabel">
                Contact the Grand Duchy ROD public counter for in-person guidance.<br>
                101 Mystic Avenue, Room 230, Eldoria Citadel &nbsp;|&nbsp; Phone: (555) 234-5678<br>
                Hours: M-F 8:30AM-5:00PM &nbsp;|&nbsp; rod@eldoria.gov
            </span>
        </div>

        <div class="footerBar">
